w2kConfigSysColdStartTime.name: w2kConfigSysColdStartTime
w2kConfigSysColdStartTime.description: &<caiW2kOs.121>The date and time that the system was last started.

w2kConfigCpuPollInterval.name: w2kConfigCpuPollInterval
w2kConfigCpuPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.122>The time (in seconds) between the polling of the processor information. Valid values are greater than or equal to 30.

w2kConfigCpuPollMethod.name: w2kConfigCpuPollMethod
w2kConfigCpuPollMethod.description: &<caiW2kOs.123>If set to 'disabled', the agent no more retrieves the processor information (not by polling, nor by get request) and sets all statuses to ok. If set to 'poll-interval-only', the agent only retrieves the information by polling, but not by get request. If set to 'poll-interval-and-query', the agent retrieves the information in both cases (polling and get request). If set to 'query-only', the agent retrieves the information for get requests only.

w2kConfigCpuLoadLag.name: w2kConfigCpuLoadLag
w2kConfigCpuLoadLag.description: &<caiW2kOs.124>The number of consecutive poll intervals that the threshold has to be (b)reached before the status changes. Valid values are greater than 0.

w2kConfigCpuLoadWarn.name: w2kConfigCpuLoadWarn
w2kConfigCpuLoadWarn.description: &<caiW2kOs.125>Warning threshold for the utilization of the processor (as percentage value of 100). Valid values are 1 to 99 and smaller than the critical threshold.

w2kConfigCpuLoadCrit.name: w2kConfigCpuLoadCrit
w2kConfigCpuLoadCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.126>Critical threshold for the utilization of the processor (as percentage value of 100). Valid values are 2 to 100 and greater than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigCpuLoadMonitor.name: w2kConfigCpuLoadMonitor
w2kConfigCpuLoadMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.127>Flag indicating whether the utilization of the processor should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigCpuLossAction.name: w2kConfigCpuLossAction
w2kConfigCpuLossAction.description: &<caiW2kOs.128>Flag defining the severity if the loss of the processor is detected or whether to remove this watcher in that case.

w2kConfigMemPollInterval.name: w2kConfigMemPollInterval
w2kConfigMemPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.129>The time (in seconds) between the polling of the memory information. Valid values are greater than or equal to 30.

w2kConfigMemPollMethod.name: w2kConfigMemPollMethod
w2kConfigMemPollMethod.description: &<caiW2kOs.130>If set to 'disabled', the agent no more retrieves the memory information (not by polling, nor by get request) and sets all statuses to ok. If set to 'poll-interval-only', the agent only retrieves the information by polling, but not by get request. If set to 'poll-interval-and-query', the agent retrieves the information in both cases (polling and get request). If set to 'query-only', the agent retrieves the information for get requests only.

w2kConfigLVolPollInterval.name: w2kConfigLVolPollInterval
w2kConfigLVolPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.131>The time (in seconds) between the polling of the logical volume information. Valid values are greater than or equal to 30.

w2kConfigLVolPollMethod.name: w2kConfigLVolPollMethod
w2kConfigLVolPollMethod.description: &<caiW2kOs.132>If set to 'disabled', the agent no more retrieves the logical volume information (not by polling, nor by get request) and sets all statuses to ok. If set to 'poll-interval-only', the agent only retrieves the information by polling, but not by get request. If set to 'poll-interval-and-query', the agent retrieves the information in both cases (polling and get request). If set to 'query-only', the agent retrieves the information for get requests only.

w2kConfigLVolAutoPollInterval.name: w2kConfigLVolAutoPollInterval
w2kConfigLVolAutoPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.133>The time (in minutes), when a new auto discovery process is started. Valid values are greater than or equal to 30 or set to -1. If set to -1, auto discovery of logical volumes will no more be made.

w2kConfigLVolFragPollInterval.name: w2kConfigLVolFragPollInterval
w2kConfigLVolFragPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.134>The time (in hours), when the fragmentation determination of the watched logical volumes is started again (triggered by the next polling or a get request). The agent will not determine the fragmentation every standard poll interval, because it is a long lasting task. Valid values are greater than or equal to 1 or set to -1. After a set on this attribute, the fragmentation determination will be started new by the next polling or by a get request. If set to -1, the fragmentation is no more polled.

w2kConfigLVolName.name: w2kConfigLVolName
w2kConfigLVolName.description: &<caiW2kOs.135>Name of the watcher to be added/removed, monitoring a logical volume with this name. If adding an auto discovery watcher, this name can be a wildcarded logical volume name filtering the logical volumes to be auto discovered (any backslash in the wildcarded name must be doubled). For each auto discovered logical volume a watcher will be created. Important: This name is case insensitive.

w2kConfigLVolAggLag.name: w2kConfigLVolAggLag
w2kConfigLVolAggLag.description: &<caiW2kOs.137>The number of consecutive poll intervals on which any status is not in the Ok or Up state, before the aggregate status changes. Valid values are greater than 0.

w2kConfigLVolSizeWarn.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeWarn
w2kConfigLVolSizeWarn.description: &<caiW2kOs.138>Warning threshold in megabytes, either for the free (by appending a 'F') or for the used logical volume size. The used size can also be defined as a percentage value of the total logical volume size (by appending a '%'). Valid values are greater than 0 and smaller (in case of 'free' greater) than the critical threshold.

w2kConfigLVolSizeCrit.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeCrit
w2kConfigLVolSizeCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.139>Critical threshold in megabytes, either for the free (by appending a 'F') or for the used logical volume size. The used size can also be defined as a percentage value of the total logical volume size (by appending a '%'). Valid values are greater than 1 and greater (in case of 'free' smaller) than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigLVolSizeMonitor.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeMonitor
w2kConfigLVolSizeMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.140>Flag indicating whether the used logical volume size should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigLVolSizeDWarn.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeDWarn
w2kConfigLVolSizeDWarn.description: &<caiW2kOs.141>Warning threshold, either for the growth (by appending a '+') or for the shrinkage (by appending a '-') or for the absolute delta in used logical volume size monitored in one poll interval. Growth, shrinkage and absolute delta can be given in megabytes or as a percentage value of the total logical volume size (by appending a '%'). Valid values are greater than 0 and smaller than the critical threshold.

w2kConfigLVolSizeDCrit.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeDCrit
w2kConfigLVolSizeDCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.142>Critical threshold, either for the growth (by appending a '+') or for the shrinkage (by appending a '-') or for the absolute delta in used logical volume size monitored in one poll interval. Growth, shrinkage and absolute delta can be given in megabytes or as a percentage value of the total logical volume size (by appending a '%'). Valid values are greater than 1 and greater than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigLVolSizeDMonitor.name: w2kConfigLVolSizeDMonitor
w2kConfigLVolSizeDMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.143>Flag indicating whether the delta in used logical volume size should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigLVolTPutWarn.name: w2kConfigLVolTPutWarn
w2kConfigLVolTPutWarn.description: &<caiW2kOs.144>Warning threshold for the throughput rate (kilobytes per second). Valid values are greater than 0 and smaller than the critical threshold.

w2kConfigLVolTPutCrit.name: w2kConfigLVolTPutCrit
w2kConfigLVolTPutCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.145>Critical threshold for the throughput rate (kilobytes per second). Valid values are greater than 1 and greater than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigLVolTPutMonitor.name: w2kConfigLVolTPutMonitor
w2kConfigLVolTPutMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.146>Flag indicating whether the throughput rate should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigLVolFragWarn.name: w2kConfigLVolFragWarn
w2kConfigLVolFragWarn.description: &<caiW2kOs.147>Warning threshold for the file fragmentation (as percentage value of 100). Valid values are 1 to 99 and smaller than the critical threshold.

w2kConfigLVolFragCrit.name: w2kConfigLVolFragCrit
w2kConfigLVolFragCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.148>Critical threshold for the file fragmentation (as percentage value of 100). Valid values are 2 to 100 and greater than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigLVolFragMonitor.name: w2kConfigLVolFragMonitor
w2kConfigLVolFragMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.149>Flag indicating whether the file fragmentation should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigLVolLossAction.name: w2kConfigLVolLossAction
w2kConfigLVolLossAction.description: &<caiW2kOs.150>Flag defining the severity if the loss of the logical volume is detected or whether to remove this watcher in that case.

w2kConfigLVolAutoTableWatcherName.name: w2kConfigLVolAutoTableWatcherName
w2kConfigLVolAutoTableWatcherName.description: &<caiW2kOs.151>Name of the watcher to be added in the auto discovery table.

w2kConfigLVolAutoTable.description: &<caiW2kOs.153>A table containing all auto discovery watchers for logical volumes.

w2kConfigLVolAutoName.description: &<caiW2kOs.156>Wildcarded logical volume name filtering the logical volumes to be auto discovered (any backslash in the wildcarded name must be doubled). For each auto discovered logical volume a watcher will be created. Important: This name is case insensitive.

w2kConfigLVolAutoButton.description: &<caiW2kOs.172>This attribute is used to remove this auto discovery watcher.

w2kConfigMntPollMethod.description: &<caiW2kOs.174>If set to 'disabled', the agent no more retrieves the mount information (not by polling, nor by get request) and sets all statuses to ok. If set to 'poll-interval-only', the agent only retrieves the information by polling, but not by get request. w2kConfigMntAutoPollInterval.description: &<caiW2kOs.175>The time (in minutes), when a new auto discovery process is started. Valid values are greater than or equal to 30 or set to -1. If set to -1, auto discovery of mounts will no more be made.

If set to 'poll-interval-and-query', the agent retrieves the information in both cases (polling and get request). If set to 'query-only', the agent retrieves the information for get requests only.

w2kConfigDfsAutoPollInterval.name: w2kConfigDfsAutoPollInterval

w2kConfigDfsName.name: w2kConfigDfsName
w2kConfigDfsName.description: &<caiW2kOs.195>Name of the watcher to be added/removed, monitoring a distributed file system link with this name. The name consists of the Dfs root name followed by the Dfs link name. These two names are concatenated by a back-slash. The single Dfs root name (without '\DfsLinkName') can also be used as watcher name, to be able to monitor all Dfs links of a Dfs root. In that case no loss action will be triggered if no Dfs link exists. If adding an auto discovery watcher, this name can be a wildcarded Dfs link name filtering the Dfs links to be auto discovered (any backslash in the wildcarded name must be doubled). For each auto discovered Dfs link a watcher will be created. Important: This name is case insensitive.

w2kConfigDfsAggLag.name: w2kConfigDfsAggLag

w2kConfigDfsReplicaCrit.name: w2kConfigDfsReplicaCrit
w2kConfigDfsReplicaCrit.description: &<caiW2kOs.199>Critical threshold for the number of unavailable replicas of the distributed file system link. Valid values are greater than 1 and greater than the warning threshold.

w2kConfigDfsReplicaMonitor.name: w2kConfigDfsReplicaMonitor
w2kConfigDfsReplicaMonitor.description: &<caiW2kOs.200>Flag indicating whether the unavailable replicas should be monitored and if so, which threshold should be compared with.

w2kConfigQuotLVolName.name: w2kConfigQuotLVolName
